I"*<p>A slow-paced style of yoga that consists of mild poses held for a longer period of time. I love yin because its goal is not to let my body land in a pose, but rather to let the pose help me better land in my body. <a class="internal-link" href="/yin-yoga-trains-the-discomfort-muscle">* Yin yoga trains the discomfort muscle</a>, which is also the most important reason I practice it.</p>

